Summary:
- GIFs now try the bundled Pillow helper predecode path before GDI+/FreeImage streaming fallback.
- The helper now writes delays.txt with per-frame delays, so GIF timing comes from Pillow metadata.
- Animated WebP still uses Quivi's RIFF delay parser because Pillow reported the first test WebP frame delay as 100 ms instead of the expected 63 ms.
- GIF dispatch now prefers FreeImage first so the helper-backed predecoded animation path is used.
- The animation scheduler now joins its worker briefly during stop/shutdown to avoid Python 2 daemon-thread shutdown messages.

Expected behavior tradeoff:
- GIFs may load for longer up front, similar to the fork and similar to our animated WebP path.
- Playback should then be smoother because frame advance no longer decodes/composes frames during steady playback.

